\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Regret-word rate by condition for GPT-4o vs.\ Gemini-2.5-Flash. Both models replicate the Deprivation$>$Neutral ordering, supporting H3. Gemini produces $\sim $2.5$\times $ higher absolute rates under deprivation ($M=1.50$ vs.\ $0.61$), suggesting model-level alignment differences modulate marker magnitude. \textit  {Key takeaway: directional cross-model replication holds; magnitude is not invariant.}}}{4}{}\protected@file@percent }
